### [James Chapter 2](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#001.md)

[James](../../../bib/kjv/jam001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">jam 2:0</span></span>

Overview

[Jam 2:1](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#001.md), It is not agreeable to
Christian profession to regard the rich, and to despise the poor
brethren; [Jam 2:13](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#013.md), rather we are to
be loving and merciful; [Jam 2:14](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#014.md), and
not to boast of faith where no deeds are; [Jam
2:17](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#017.md), which is but a dead faith; [Jam
2:19](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#019.md), the faith of the devils; [Jam
2:21](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#021.md), not of Abraham; [Jam
2:25](../../../bib/kjv/jam002.htm#025.md), nor Rahab.

